<subSubSection pageNumber="282" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="282">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="282">Note:</emphasis>
As noted by Dudley (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="282">J. Arnold Arbor.</emphasis>
45: 65. 1964), this is an illegitimate replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1753)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Clypeola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alyssoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="282">Clypeola alyssoides</emphasis>
L. (1753)
</taxonomicName>
. However, Botschantzev (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="282">Novosti Sist. Vyssh. Rast.</emphasis>
15: 150-151. 1985) incorrectly treats it as the correct name for 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Clypeola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alyssoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="282">C. alyssoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1753)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Agaricaceae" genus="Clypeola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="campestris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="282">C. campestris</emphasis>
L. (1753)
</taxonomicName>
, both of which he treats as ambiguous. See further notes on this name by German (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="282">Turczaninowia</emphasis>
6(1): 53-55. 2003).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
